Project: Investigate a Soccer Dataset¶

Table of Contents¶

  • Introduction

  • Conclusions

¶

Introduction¶

This soccer database comes from Kaggle. It records information on leagues, matches, players and teams from 11 European countries between 2008 and 2016. This report will focus on soccer players's attibutes, and try to answer the following questions:

  • Who are the top 5 rated soccer players?
  • Which attributies are highly correlated to players's overall rating?
  • Which players had the most penalties?
In [587]:

%matplotlib inline

Research Question 2: Which attributies are highly correlated to players' overall rating?¶

In this part, I will filter and take only the subset of the relevant features by processing the following steps:

  • First plot the correlation heatmap
  • Look at the correlation of independent variables with variable overall_rating.
  • Select features which have correlation of above 0.35 (taking absolute value) with variable overall_rating.

Limitation¶

  • In this report, I only focus on Player and Player_Attributes tables. In the future, I can reacher further on how the players contributed to matches with their teams or leagues.
  • The Player table has 212 repeated names. To avoid confusion, I changed the repeated names as their name. There is no additional efforts on checking the correction of each name except duplications.
  • The Player_Attributes table contains thousand missing data. I had to drop the rows having any missing value inputs, which may have impact on evaluation of some idividual player performances.

Conclusions¶

Based on my data analysis on player's attributes, I can draw following conclusions:

  • The top 5 players having higest overall rating are Lionel Messi, Cristiano Ronaldo, Franck Ribery, Andres Iniesta, and Zlatan Ibrahimovic, and their rating are 92.19, 91.28, 88.56, 88,32, and 88.29, respectively.
  • The distribution of player's overall rating is normal, and player's potential, reactions, vision, long_passing and penalties are positive related to his overall rating.
  • Player Alessio Cerci has most penalties. He has his best perfomace regard to penalties in 2014. In addition, his penalties shows very stong relationship with his rating.
